inscription: Above figure's head, in the image: Autumnus | Below figure's PR foot, in the image: HG. Inuet. / 3 | Inscribed on plate around circumference: Pomifer Autumnus turgentibus vuidus vuis. Mi pleno cornu copia larga fluit. Et lautis mensis bellaria bella ministro. AEquat dum nocti pendula libra diem
provenance: Private collection, United States; (Childs Gallery, Boston); sold to MIA, 2007.
title: Allegory of Autumn
